 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucloudien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cloudien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(2/18/02 6:38:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cloudk.clara.net/storage/zidane2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: my 2cp :)</span><hr size=1> You can cast spells with ALT+(spell number) so I never set up hotkeys for those except on my bard twink (it only really helps with twisting)<br>
Also if you hold ALT, it'll show you the number of each spell and its name.<br>
<br>
Here's mine so far ---<br>
<br>
Page 1:<br>
1: &quot;Puller&quot; - /assist PullerNameHere (for groups)<br>
2: &quot;Assist&quot; - /assist  (on its own.  Nice for 'assisting' the target mob and placing a damage shield on its target)<br>
3-0: Pet commands (Attack, sit, report health, back off, taunt on, taunt off, follow me, guard here)<br>
<br>
Attack in red, back off in green for visibility.  Assist keys on 1 and 2 to prevent fumbling around the keyboard in hectic group situations.<br>
<br>
Page 2:<br>
1: &quot;Nukes&quot; - /book 1<br>
2: &quot;Pet&quot; - /book 3<br>
3: &quot;Summ1&quot; - /book 5<br>
4: &quot;Summ2&quot; - /book 7<br>
5: &quot;Buffs&quot; - /book 9<br>
6: &quot;Utils&quot; - /book 11<br>
<br>
Page 3:<br>
Sense heading, /corpse and stuff<br>
<br>
<br>
Common hotkey routine in a group, when a fresh pull arrives:<br>
Shift+1, 1, 2, Alt+6, 1, 3, Alt+1, Ctrl+B<br>
<br>
This turns to hotkey bank 1, assists the main puller, 'assist's his Chosen Mob (which targets the groupmember it's currently hitting), casts a damage shield on said groupmember, assists the main puller again, sics pet on Chosen Mob, nukes the Mob, and opens the spellbook to med.<br>
<br>
Obviously, after 35, Ctrl+B will be replaced with Ctrl+S <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
